<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="117" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,794,1929,2049]" pageId="14" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,308,1929,1953]" pageId="14" pageNumber="117">Etymology</emphasis>
: The specific epithet is an adjective derived from the Latin noun auricula (diminutive of auris: ear) and alludes to the shapes of the apical internal structures of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
